Blocks.Text: 1. In this track, we use representative object trackers with both CNN-based backbones and vision
transformer-based backbones to track each animal instance across the video clips, giving each animal's
ground truth bounding box in the first frame.
It can be observed that vision transformer-based trackers obtain slightly better performance compared with
2. Even without further finetuning, the shared backbone model ViTTrack+ obtains superior performance in
3. These results imply the potential of plain vision transformers as a foundation model for simultaneously
serving multiple vision tasks, which is of great significance and deserves more research in future work.
